Package ohos.interwork.utils

Class PacMapEx

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.interwork.utils.PacMapEx
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ParcelableEx, Sequenceable

    public class PacMapEx
extends Object
implements ParcelableEx, Sequenceable
    Defines the structure for the data packets transmitted between processes across platforms. In a HarmonyOS process, your application data is stored as key-value pairs in a PacMapEx object. This object will be marshalled and then transmitted to a process in another platform. After receiving the marshalled object, that process will unmarshal it and then read the data.
    Since:
    3

      • PacMapEx

        public PacMapEx​(PacMapEx outMap,
                boolean isDeepCopy)
        Construct a PacMapEx Object from another PacMapEx, which can make a deep copy if the second parameter is true.

        Note: deep copy only support primitive Data types, Object, and array of them, and also an inner PacMapEx. If the PacMapEx has a map inner, the map will not be deep copied. even if the isDeepCopy is true.

        Parameters:
        isDeepCopy - Indicates whether to do a deep copy. if set true, will do a deep copy.
        Since:
        3
